title: My Song Is Love Unknown
author: F. Allaben
presentation: v1 v2 v3 v4 v5 v6

v1: And tears of praise Thy griefs compel.
What love and grace illume Thy face
v2: What scorn and outrage Thee befell:
Deep shame and woe, rude blow on blow,
v3: But oh, what grief, what agony,
Burst over Thee on Calv'ry's tree,
v4: Creation's Head is He who bled—
v5: E'en now from saints, in concord sweet,
For, O, 'tis meet glad songs should greet
v6: But when Thy glorious face we see,
How shall the bursting paean swell!
Our souls shall be outpoured for Thee—
